{{Expand Spanish|Spanisharticletitle|date=March 2015}} {{use dmy dates|date=March 2016}} {{Infobox artist | honorific_prefix = | name = Ximena Zomosa | honorific_suffix = | image = <!-- just the pagename, without the File:/Image: prefix or [[brackets]] --> | image_size = | alt = | caption = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | birth_name = <!--only use if different from name--> | birth_date = 1966 <!-- {{Birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} for living artists, {{Birth date|YYYY|MM|DD}} for dead --> | birth_place = [[Santiago de Chile|Santiago]], [[Chile]] | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | death_place = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} --> | nationality = | education = [[Pontifical Catholic University of Chile|Universidad Católica de Chile]] | alma_mater = | known_for = | notable_works = | style = | movement = | spouse = | awards = <!-- {{awd|award|year|title|role|name}} (optional) --> | elected = | patrons = | memorials = | website = <!-- {{URL|Example.com}} --> | module = }}
'''Ximena Zomosa''' (born 1966, [[Santiago de Chile|Santiago]], [[Chile]]) is a [[Visual arts|visual artist]] and [[curator]] who works in [[contemporary art]]<ref name=ref_11 /> and [[conceptual art]],<ref name=ref_1 /> whose work demonstrates — from the perspective of [[gender]]<ref name=ref_3 /> — a discourse that is fundamentally feminine.<ref name=ref_4 /> She acted in a managerial and curatorial capacity at the Balmaceda Youth Art Gallery, a space for art by emerging Chilean artists.<ref name=ref_10>{{Cite web | title = "Welcome Tour" instalación de Ximena Zomosa | url = http://www.estoy.cl/agenda/exposiciones/669 | access-date = 28 June 2013 }}</ref>
Zomosa studied art at the [[Pontifical Catholic University of Chile]], which complemented her studies at various Chilean universities.<ref name=ref_1 /> Her work is characterized by "la originalidad mostrada en el empleo de materiales sacados de la vida cotidiana y dispuestos en instalaciones inusuales (...). En su afán transformatorio, es evidente un sentido autobiográfico e irónico frente a lo femenino y lo doméstico" ("originality demonstrated in the use of materials from everyday life and displayed in unusual installations (...). In her eager transformation, there is a sense of the autobiographical and irony in the face of that which is feminine and that which is domestic").<ref name=ref_1 />
In 2004, Zomosa received the [[Altazor Award|Altazor Award of the National Arts]] in the category of Installations and Video Art for ''Colección de la artista'' (''Artist's Collection'').<ref name=ref_2>{{Cite web | title = Ximena Zomosa - Colección de la artista | author = Altazor – Premio a las Artes Nacionales | work = Artes Visuales - Instalación y Videoarte | url = http://www.premioaltazor.cl/ximena-zomosa-coleccion-de-la-artista/ | access-date = 24 June 2013 }}</ref>
Throughout her career, Zomosa has participated in solo exhibitions as well as exhibitions featuring other artists, including V Bienal de Estandartes in [[Tijuana]] (2008); ''Concours Matisse 1992,'' ''Concours Matisse 1994,'' and ''II Biennial Premio Gunthe,'' in the [[Chilean National Museum of Fine Arts]] (1992, 1994, and 1995, respectively); ''Última Generación'' at the [[:es:Museo de Arte Moderno Chiloé|Chiloé Museum of Modern Art]] (1995), ''Everyday'' at the [[Art Gallery of New South Wales]] for the [[Biennale of Sydney]] (1998); ''El Lugar dentro'' at the [[:es:Casa Colorada|Casa Colorada Museum]] (1999);<ref name=ref_12>{{Cite web | title = Notas de Arte | publisher = El Mercurio | work = Artes y letras | url = http://diario.elmercurio.com/detalle/index.asp?id={434cee0f-a6b8-4306-b270-217766d52a39} | date = 26 September 1999 | access-date = 18 April 2010 }}</ref> ''Proyecto de Borde'' at the [[:es:Museo de Arte Contemporáneo de Valdivia|Valdivia Museum of Contemporary Art]] (1999); ''Project N11, Muro Sur arte chileno contemporáneo'' for the la Biennale of [[Shanghai]] (2004); ''Portable Affairs, Project of a Boundary'' at [[Artspace Sydney|Artspace Sydney Visual Arts Centre]] in [[Sydney]] (2005); and ''Arte Mujer y Compromiso Político'' at the [[:es:Museo de la Solidaridad Salvador Allende|Salvador Allende Museum of Solidarity]] (2009),<ref name=ref_7>{{Cite web | title = Mujer, Arte y Compromiso: Visibilizando la solidaridad de las artistas del mundo | publisher = Museo de la Solidaridad Salvador Allende | url = http://www.fundacionsalvadorallende.cl/noticiasalida.php?num=2360 | dead-url = yes | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100107080915/http://www.fundacionsalvadorallende.cl/noticiasalida.php?num=2360 | date = 7 January 2010 | access-date = 28 June 2013 | archive-date = 7 January 2010 }}</ref> and other exhibitions in the [[United States]], [[Latin America]], [[Australia]], and [[Europe]].<ref name=ref_11>{{Cite book | title = Memorias visuales: arte contemporáneo en Chile | last = Valdés | first = Adriana | publisher = Ediciones/Metales Pesados | pages = 432 | date = 2006 }}</ref><ref name=ref_1>{{Cite web | title = Ximena Zomosa (1966-) | publisher = Biblioteca del Museo Nacional de Bellas Artes | work = APCh, Artistas plásticos chilenos | url = http://www.artistasplasticoschilenos.cl/biografia.aspx?itmid=912 | access-date = 24 June 2013 }}</ref><ref name=ref_3>{{Cite web | title = "Project of a Boundary": Artistas chilenas exponen en Australia | author1-last = Rozas | author1-first = Maril | work = El Mercurio (Chile), Actividad cultural | url = http://diario.elmercurio.com/detalle/index.asp?id={8bc44d32-d508-49bd-805d-1f403c5c1901 | date = 11 July 2005 | access-date = 24 June 2013 }}}</ref><ref name=ref_4>{{Cite web | title = Artes visuales: Novedosas propuestas en torno a la mujer | author1-last = rdenas | author1-first = Elisa | publisher = El Mercurio | work = Actividad cultural | url = http://diario.elmercurio.com/detalle/index.asp?id={a20d5a21-a279-4acb-a925-e82487c350fa} | date = 12 March 2003 | access-date = 24 June 2013 }}</ref>
